[![VIEWPOINT 16 - ARISE](https://www.pantone.com/media/wysiwyg/categories/color-trends-education-viewpoint-colour-16.webp?auto=webp&format=pjpg&quality=85)](https://www.pantone.com/products/trend-books/viewpoint-colour-issue-16-brainpower)

### [VIEWPOINT COLOUR](https://www.pantone.com/products/trend-books/viewpoint-colour-issue-16-brainpower)

In BRAINPOWER we explore the biological and psychological relationship between color, the brain, and creativity. By affecting mood, memory, and mental state, color profoundly influences and shapes how we think, feel, and create. In 2026 color transcends its traditional role into an even more powerful tool for emotional connection and well-being. This shift towards emotionally driven color palettes speaks to a world craving comfort, unity, and empowerment. Color now nurtures us on a deeper level, transforming spaces, packaging and products into experiences that connect, uplift, and reflect our shared human journey in a profound way.

